<text>The voiced alveolo-palatal sibilant fricative is a type of consonantal sound, used in some spoken languages. The symbol in the International Phonetic Alphabet that represents this sound is (&quot;z&quot;, plus the curl also found in its voiceless counterpart ), and the equivalent X-SAMPA symbol is codice_1. It is the sibilant equivalent of the voiced palatal fricative, and as such it can be transcribed in IPA with .

