<doc id="524886" wikidata="Q1137793" url="?curid=524886" title="Voiceless epiglottal trill">
<text>The voiceless epiglottal or pharyngeal trill, or voiceless epiglottal fricative, is a type of consonantal sound, used in some spoken languages. The symbol in the International Phonetic Alphabet that represents this sound is , a small capital version of the Latin letter h, and the equivalent X-SAMPA symbol is codice_1.

The glyph is homoglyphic with the lowercase Cyrillic letter En (н) in roman typeface, but distinct in italic.

==Features==
Features of the voiceless epiglottal trill/fricative:


