<doc id="524909" wikidata="Q1808098" url="?curid=524909" title="Voiced dental and alveolar implosives">
<text>The voiced alveolar implosive is a type of consonantal sound, used in some spoken languages. The symbol in the International Phonetic Alphabet that represents this sound is . The IPA symbol is lowercase letter &quot;d&quot; with a rightward hook protruding from the upper right of the letter.

The voiced dental implosive may be found in the Jhangvi dialect of Punjabi and has the symbol .

