<text>The voiced velar implosive is a type of consonantal sound, used in some spoken languages. The symbol in the International Phonetic Alphabet that represents this sound is , and the equivalent X-SAMPA symbol is codice_1. It is familiar to English speakers as the sound made when mimicking the &#x27;gulping&#x27; of water.

